  "text": "The London musician returns after last year’s Homeless N***a Pop MusicJim Legxacy, photo by FidelJim Legxacy is back with new music. Watch the video for new track “Aggressive” below. It marks the British multi-hyphenate’s debut for XL Recordings, after a string of self-releases, including last year’s breakout track “Old Place.” The video, directed by Fidel, was shot on Blackberry.“Aggressive” follows Legxacy’s July single “Nothings Changed (!).” He co-produced the new song with AOD, Joe Stanley, and Tendai. The track samples British rapper Chipmunk’s 2009 single “Oopsy Daisy.”Next year, Legxacy plans to release a mixtape called Black British Music (2024). Read about his 2023 record, Homeless N***a Pop Music, in Pitchfork’s rundown of “The 100 Best Albums of the 2020s So Far.”Jazz Monroe is a music and culture writer based in London. His work also appears in The Guardian, The Independent, and elsewhere.Hot LinksA daily roundup of the most important stories in music, and a listening guide every Friday",
